From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Oct 2012 22:05:48 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v4 01/25] ethernet: Convert dev_printk(KERN_<LEVEL> to
 dev_<level>(
Patch-mainline: v3.8-rc1
Git-commit: f7b4fb22b838f895ce9fa994f0ef4f7f541f5266 (partial)
References: bsc#909575 FATE#317552

dev_<level> calls take less code than dev_printk(KERN_<LEVEL>
and reducing object size is good.
Coalesce formats for easier grep.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: David Chang <dchang@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb3/common.h |    7 +++----
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb3/common.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/chelsio/cxgb3/common.h
@@ -42,10 +42,9 @@
 #include <linux/mdio.h>
 #include "version.h"
 
-#define CH_ERR(adap, fmt, ...)   dev_err(&adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ## __VA_ARGS__)
-#define CH_WARN(adap, fmt, ...)  dev_warn(&adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ## __VA_ARGS__)
-#define CH_ALERT(adap, fmt, ...) \
-	dev_printk(KERN_ALERT, &adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ## __VA_ARGS__)
+#define CH_ERR(adap, fmt, ...)   dev_err(&adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__)
+#define CH_WARN(adap, fmt, ...)  dev_warn(&adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__)
+#define CH_ALERT(adap, fmt, ...) dev_alert(&adap->pdev->dev, fmt, ##__VA_ARGS__)
 
 /*
  * More powerful macro that selectively prints messages based on msg_enable.
